+/// is MORE lenient than the declared wire contract. A bare number is read as a
+/// **Julian day** (`strftime('%s','2451545.0')` → `946728000`, i.e. year 2000)
+/// and `strftime('%s','0')` resolves to a pre-year-0000 epoch — so non-ISO input
